Slide â€” DR Environment Implementation Summary

We have successfully built a complete Azure-based Disaster Recovery environment with the following components:

Network Setup: VNet, Subnets, IP Prefix, Public IPs

Secure Connectivity: IPSec Tunnel, VPN Gateways, Azure Firewall, NSGs, Bastion Host

Compute & Storage: SQL Server VM, Storage Accounts, Containers, Golden Images

DNS & Identity:

Full internal DNS architecture replicated from on-prem

Domain Controller deployment for DR authentication

Active Directory replication (users, groups, policies)

DNS zones, A-records, PTR-records, SRV-records recreated in DR

Ensured name resolution, domain join capability, Kerberos/NTLM authentication flow

Validated forwarders, conditional forwarders, and DNS health checks


Replication & Recovery: Azure Site Recovery (ASR) with policies, VM replication, and recovery plans

Automation: DR infra automated using Terraform, Bash, Azure CLI, executed via Automation Accounts


Outcome:
A secure, scalable, and fully automated DR environment with complete network, compute, storage, and identity stack aligned with on-prem, enabling seamless failover and business continuity.


